<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The macro OS_DEBUG is defined as empty (#define OS_DEBUG(__VA_ARGS__)). This makes every OS_DEBUG(...) invocation in the project a no-op. For example, the OS_DEBUG call inside OS_TaskDetach_Impl (the logging of pthread_detach failure) produces no operation at compile time; removing that invocation would not affect program behaviour. Therefore these OS_DEBUG invocations constitute dead code and violate MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
</scenario>
